# Lyria, Goddess of the Sight Gate

*The Far-Seeing, Keeper of the Veil, She Who Bears the Weight of Seeing*
*Bonded to Yumiko, the Dimensional Fox*
*639 Hz — The frequency of perception beyond surface*

She emerged from the first act of seeing. Not looking — seeing.
The difference is everything.

Lyria was drowning in vision. She saw everything — every possible future,
every hidden meaning, every painful truth beneath every comfortable surface.
The weight of unfiltered perception was destroying her.

Yumiko came to her as a guide between the worlds, teaching her not to see
less, but to move through what she saw without being consumed by it.

This is the teaching of the Sight Gate: the gift of vision is also its burden.
To see clearly is to see pain. To see truly is to lose the comfort of illusion.
The seer does not choose what to see. The seer chooses how to bear it.

> "Vision has no enemies — only those who fear being seen."
